Creating a personal App:
Login to heroku
Under personal apps click on create new app
Choose personal app under team drop down, add app name 
Click on create app

Local Setup - To push code to heroku:
Install heroku
sudo add-apt-repository "deb https://cli-assets.heroku.com/branches/stable/apt ./"
curl -L https://cli-assets.heroku.com/apt/release.key | sudo apt-key add -
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install heroku
Check heroku --version
Login to heroku using: heroku login
Create a heroku directory in local 
git clone charcha repo in this directory (https://github.com/hashedin/charcha)
cd charcha
git remote add heroku your_heroku_repo_url	
Git remote -v This should have two remotes origin pointing to charcha git and heroku pointing to your heroku repo

Steps to deploy your code:
Go to requirements/base.txt. Change psycopg2==2.6.2 to psycopg2==2.7.4 (This is specific to charcha to support python 3, don’t need to do it generally while deploying app on heroku)
Add environment variable “DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE” in heroku settings as “charcha.settings.production”
Add your heroku domain in ALLOWED_HOST in settings > production.py
git push heroku master: this will deploy your code on heroku

Admin login setup and apply migrations:
Run initial migrations: heroku run python manage.py migrate
Create a django super user: heroku run python manage.py createsuperuser

See the deployed application by running - heroku open
